The paper discusses various natural language processing tasks such as Answer Sentence Selection, Semantic Text Scoring, Recognizing Textual Entailment, and Paraphrasing, which are all subfields of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes new baselines using convolutional, recurrent, and attention-based neural models, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the problem of evaluating randomized models, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and proposes a statistically grounded methodology. Finally, the paper introduces a unified open-source software framework, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
